id: pm-wc0d
title: Add 120-file unit-test cap governance test to ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts
description: "The 120-file-per-directory cap for tests/unit/ is enforced by scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs (--max-files-per-dir 120) and is a documented rule. However, no test in tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts or elsewhere validates that the current unit file count stays at or below 120. With 122 files already in tests/unit/, the gate should fire soon if new tests keep being added — but contributors won't know this until the static gate fails in CI."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:ci","area:tests",governance,quality-gate
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:34.173Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-19T21:57:31.644Z"
author: audit-docs-tests-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- A test or note confirms whether 122 files in tests/unit/ is expected to pass the static gate (e.g. subdirectory counting only, or the cap is directory-specific)\n- If tests/unit/ has exceeded the cap: add a failing test + doc explaining the merge strategy\n- If tests/unit/ has a subdirectory that splits load (tests/unit/core/, tests/unit/commands/): document the strategy in TESTING.md"
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: "tests/unit/ was restructured into per-area subdirectories (commands/, core/, cli/, mcp/, ...), so the 120-file cap is now per-directory and the largest dir (src/cli/commands, 65) is well under it. New contract test reuses the gate's own collectTypeScriptFiles/checkDirectoryLoad against the live repo (asserts 0 violations) and pins MAX_FILES_PER_DIRECTORY to the gate's default-120 literal so the two cannot drift. TESTING.md documents the cap + placement rule."
expected_result: Confirm 120-file cap status and document the subdirectory split strategy.
actual_result: "Premise of '122 flat files' is stale post-restructure; cap is per-directory, repo compliant; governance test + TESTING.md note added."
