close_reason: Added directory-load cap governance contract to tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts + documented the tests/unit subdirectory split in TESTING.md.
body: "## Context\nCurrent test file count: ls tests/unit/ | wc -l = 122. The static-quality-gate.mjs applies --max-files-per-dir 120 globally (line 338). So tests/unit/ may already be at the limit.\n\nci-workflow-contract.spec.ts validates pinned action SHAs, CI gate matrix alignment, etc. but has no assertion about tests/unit/ file count.\n\nThe governance rule from memory: 'tests/unit has a 120-file governance cap (merge, don’t add)'. The fact that it is already at 122 files may mean the static gate is failing, or the gate is not recursive to subdirectories. Either way this should be validated explicitly.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- A test or note confirms whether 122 files in tests/unit/ is expected to pass the static gate (e.g. subdirectory counting only, or the cap is directory-specific)\n- If tests/unit/ has exceeded the cap: add a failing test + doc explaining the merge strategy\n- If tests/unit/ has a subdirectory that splits load (tests/unit/core/, tests/unit/commands/): document the strategy in TESTING.md\n\n## Evidence\nls tests/unit/ | wc -l = 122; tests/unit/core/ and tests/unit/commands/ subdirectory exists per ls output; scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs line 338: maxFilesPerDirectory = 120"
